properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 18 at 3:05PM CST until January 19 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Grand Forks ND
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning, light snow continues as
well as blowing snow causing low visibility. Additional snow
accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 35
mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected. Wind chills as low as 35 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of central, northwest and west central
Minnesota.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, until 6 PM CST this
evening. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 6 PM this evening
to noon CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could reduce visibility at times. The cold wind chills
could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10
minutes.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

The latest road conditions for North Dakota can be found at
dot.nd.gov/travel and for Minnesota at 511mn.org, or by calling
5 1 1 in either state.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON CST SUNDAY
